I would like to question the use of the neutral MOO3 in the liquid
phase.  Together with Cs+ and MoO4-2 and with almost 2/1 site rations
in the liquid it will be very difficult to extablish the fraction of
the MoO3 in the liquid.  Small variations can create large changes in
chemical potetials if the composition of the liquid liquid is on the
line between MoO2 and CsO2.  And I think that is the case, the liquid
is amost only Cs+1 in the cation sites and almost only MoO4-2 in the
anion sublattice.

I know the Mo-O system is complicated and asume Christine has proposed
this model.  Try to skip the neutral MoO3 species.
